    "Knowledge distillation: Knowledge distillation is the process of transferring knowledge from a large model (teacher) to a smaller one (student).",
    "In our case, the teacher is the fully fine-tuned model, and the student is the model resulting from iterative pruning.",
    "We translate the in-domain data with the teacher model to augment the authentic data.",
    "As the process can result in duplicate translations, we remove duplicate segments from the training data.",
